Process Population Estimates Data for New Jersey

Source: R/pop_estimates.R
process_pop_estimates.Rd

Downloads and processes population estimates data for New Jersey counties. Data is obtained from the Census Bureau's Population Estimates Program.

process_pop_estimates(
  years = c(2021, 2022, 2023),
  file_types = c("agesex", "alldata", "syasex"),
  state_fips = "34",
  save_to_db = TRUE
)

Arguments

years

Numeric vector. Years to process data for (e.g., c(2021, 2022, 2023)).

file_types

Character vector. Types of estimates files to process. Options include 'agesex' (age and sex), 'alldata' (all demographic data), and 'syasex' (single-year age and sex).

state_fips

Character. State FIPS code. Default is "34" for New Jersey.

save_to_db

Logical. Whether to save data to the census database. Default is TRUE.

Value

A list of data frames, one for each file type requested. If save_to_db is TRUE, also saves to the census database.

Examples

if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
# Process population estimates for 2021-2023, all file types
pop_data <- process_pop_estimates(c(2021, 2022, 2023))

# Process only age-sex data for 2022
pop_data <- process_pop_estimates(2022, file_types = "agesex")
} # }
